// Onboarding DB Service
// Manages two SQLite databases for developer onboarding: full-text search and progress tracking.

Databases live at {project}/.collab/onboarding/ (gitignored).
index.db holds an FTS5 virtual table over topic content files (conceptual, technical, files).
progress.db holds users, per-user topic progress, notes, and a path_progress table.
Both databases are opened lazily. index.db is rebuilt automatically when any topic file
is newer than the current index.

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.constructor(project)                                  EXPORT
  Store the project path and set the onboarding directory path.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.ensureIndex() -> void
  Create the onboarding directory if needed. Compare the index.db mtime against all topic
  content files. IF rebuild is needed (or index is missing), drop and recreate the
  topic_fts FTS5 table using the porter/unicode61 tokenizer, then insert all
  conceptual.md, technical.md, and files.md content for every topic directory.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.search(q, scope) -> SearchResult[]
  CALLS: OnboardingDbService.ensureIndex (onboarding-db)
  Ensure the index is up to date. Escape the query for FTS5 syntax.
  Query topic_fts MATCH with an optional IN clause to scope to specific topics.
  Return up to 20 results with HTML snippet highlights (using <mark> tags), ordered by rank.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.ensureProgressDb() -> Database
  Open progress.db and run the schema creation SQL if it hasn't been opened yet.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.createUser(name) -> User
  Insert a new user by name and return the created user with id and createdAt.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.listUsers() -> User[]
  Return all users ordered by name.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.getUser(id) -> User | null
  Look up a user by id. Return null if not found.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.markProgress(userId, topic, status) -> void
  Insert or replace a progress row for the user+topic combination with the given status
  (explored or skipped) and current timestamp.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.deleteProgress(userId, topic) -> void
  Remove the progress row for the user+topic combination.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.getUserProgress(userId) -> ProgressEntry[]
  Return all progress rows for the user.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.getNotes(userId, topic) -> Note[]
  Return all notes for a user+topic combination, ordered by created_at descending.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.addNote(userId, topic, content) -> Note
  Insert a note and return the created Note including all timestamps.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.editNote(noteId, content) -> void
  Update the note content and set updated_at to the current time.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.deleteNote(noteId) -> void
  Delete the note by id.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.getTeam() -> TeamMember[]
  Query all users joined with their progress counts and last active timestamps.
  For each user, also fetch the list of explored topic names. Return the combined result.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingDbService.close() -> void
  Close both databases and null out their references.
